msg: OS/2: Remove the apr_pollset_t from apr_file_t. File handles can't be polled

author: wrowe
msg: Unix propagates the fname from the apr_file_t to apr_file_info_t
on an apr_file_info_get() call.  Do the same on Win32, but be
warned that this is informative, and is not a canonical representation.
